And also see:
https://7sur7.cd/index.php/2020/04/12/nord-kivu-un-nouveau-cas-de-deces-debola-enregistre-beni
Health officials have announced that the necessary arrangements have already been made to cut off all transmission chains, adding that around 100 suspected cases who were in contact with the 1st patient have been listed for immediate follow-up. [Note that the WHO reports 215 contacts of the 1st case compared to the 100 reported here.]

The age of the 2nd fatal case, a child of 11 years or 11 months, is not at all clear, as pointed out in https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/ebola/: "This report raises an immediate question: How old was the 2nd Ebola case, 11 months, or 11 years? Reuters cites WHO as the source for the case being a baby. 7sur7.cd cites "medical authorities" as the source for the child being 11. I have no idea which is correct, but I hope we'll learn more about both cases. It's also worth noting that "young people" in the northeast DR Congo continue to be hostile to Ebola response teams. Some things never change."]

- Tue 14 Apr 2020
[Crof's blog via Actualite (Google trans. edited)]
https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/ebola/

DRC Ebola: Secure burial of 11-year-old girl carried out

The Ebola response team announced on Mon [13 Apr 2020] that the dignified and secure burial of the 11-year-old girl who died in Beni has been completed. Her body had been kept in the morgue of the Beni General Reference Hospital.

The same source reports that 32 contacts were pre-listed around this case, including 4 family members (her mother already vaccinated), 2 motorcycle drivers, 7 co-tenants, 17 co-patients, and 2 nursing staff. The teams continue the listing and the investigations in order to determine the circumstances of contamination.

