Mary Marshall <mjm2020@googlemail.com>

[The genetics of the virus detected in the 3 latest cases may provide information on the origin of these recent cases after an apparent gap of more than 7 weeks without reported activity. The virus may have been circulating at a very low, undetectable level. It is hopeful that there won't be extensive spread since these recent cases have a single source, and contacts have been identified. - Mod.LK]

- 11 Apr 2020
[7sur7 (Google trans. abridged, edited)]
https://7sur7.cd/2020/04/11/beni-ebola-la-societe-civile-exige-le-deterrement-du-nouveau-cas-confirme-pour-une


Beni-Ebola: Civil society demands the unearthing of the new [1st] confirmed case "for an expertise in 3 laboratories"

Beni's president of civil society, Kizito Bin Hangi has stepped up to the plate after the declaration of the new case of Ebola in the region, 2 days before the end of the epidemic in the Democratic Republic of Congo.

Local civil society demands re-examining the samples to put an end to rumors of a case being created.

"We have received lamentations and complaints from both sides of the population, even the doctors and even the family of the deceased after the new case of Ebola in Beni. The body must be dug up at the expense of the response, the samples taken must be sent to 3 laboratories for comparison, including that of Mangina, Butembo and Katwa, in order to be reassured that this is indeed the confirmed case," he said.

"I call all the people having been in direct contact with the deceased person to present themselves to the response teams in order to pass the test so as not to intensify the virus in the community."

It should be recalled that a new case of Ebola was declared in the city of Beni on Fri 10 Apr 2020. However, unofficial reports say there is a 2nd case in the area [and as of 13 Apr 2020, a 3rd case].

[Byline: Bantou Kapanza Son]

